<CSSTransition-property>
<summary>
The <strong><c>transition-property</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> property sets the CSS properties to which a <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_transitions/Using_CSS_transitions">transition effect</see> should be applied.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/transition-property.html")</para><para>If you specify a shorthand property (e.g., <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background">background</see>), all of its longhand sub-properties that can be animated will be.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_transitions/Using_CSS_transitions">Using CSS transitions</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/'transition'">'transition'</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/'transition-duration'">'transition-duration'</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/'transition-timing-function'">'transition-timing-function'</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/'transition-delay'">'transition-delay'</see><br/>-<see cref="TransitionEvent."/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-property"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</CSSTransition-property>
